During his reign, Shoon VI saw to the expansion of both the magical resources of his empire and its intelligence-gathering capabilities. The empire thrived under his rule compared to its status under past rulers.

{{fq
| float  = left
| text   = Train my warriors and their progeny for the glory of the Imperium until one claims the ''[[belt of Iltaker]]''.
| source = Emperor Shoon VI's orders to the [[Champion of Iltakar]]{{Cite dungeon/127/Vampires of Waterdeep: Dungeon of the Crypt|74}}
}}
Five years before his death, Shoon VI completed crafting of a [[battle horror]] [[construct]] called the [[Champion of Iltakar]]. Its purpose was to serve as a trainer of the greatest gladiators of the arenas of [[Iltakar]] in [[Shoonach]].

Shoon VI also crafted the ''[[belt of Iltaker]]'' in the same year, a powerful magical belt to be awarded to the Empire's most valiant arena champion.{{Cite dungeon/127/Vampires of Waterdeep: Dungeon of the Crypt|75}}
